<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="eyebrow">HOW ENGAGEMENTS WORK</div>
        <div class="prose">
            <p>Most engagements start with strategy and grow into ongoing work. Every organization's communities are different, so we scope each engagement together — starting with where you are and where your buyers actually gather.</p>
            <p>Pricing is a conversation, not a page. Tell us what you're trying to do and we'll tell you what it takes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
            <details>
                <summary>Can you measure community marketing?</summary>
                <p>Yes: share of voice, qualified traffic, sentiment, branded search lift, and the conversations we can point to. We'll tell you what we can and can't attribute.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>Does this work for our kind of organization?</summary>
                <p>Almost certainly. B2B startups, consumer brands, nonprofits, public figures — if the people you care about gather somewhere and talk, community marketing works. Niche, high-trust rooms are where it works best, and B2B is where we've gone deepest.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>Can't we just do this ourselves?</summary>
                <p>You can. Most teams don't have the time to earn standing in a dozen communities without tripping the shill alarm. That's what we're for.</p>
            </details>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

